A magistrates’ court in Ilorin, Kwara State, has ordered the remand of a man over offences bordering on rape and theft. The suspect, Muhammad Bello, alongside his cohort, Chumo, who is at large, attacked one Doris Emmanuel who was on her way to the farm to pick cashew nuts in Oko Ode community in Ifelodun Local Government Area. According to the Police First Information Report (PFIR), Bello and Chumo, armed with a cutlass and a knife, accosted their victim in the bush, and Bello raped and injured her with the knife while Chumo held her legs. The charge sheet added that, “Doris was later rescued from her attackers who took to their heels after they saw one Azeez Balogun who heard her screaming. “Chumo, while escaping the scene, stole the victim’s Tecno phone.” The magistrate, Afusat Alege, ordered the remand of the suspect and adjourned the case to April 13. 